<h2 id=3D"id-11.SD:ForeignCurrencyAccountProductChannels-TechnicalDebt">Tec=
hnical Debt</h2>
<p></p>
<p>N/A</p>
<h1 id=3D"id-11.SD:ForeignCurrencyAccountProductChannels-Solution"><span>So=
lution</span></h1>
<h2 id=3D"id-11.SD:ForeignCurrencyAccountProductChannels-SolutionOverview">=
<span>Solution Overview</span></h2>
<p>This solution outlines the foundational changes required from the channe=
l end to support the Foreign Currency Account product across product setup,=
 servicing, and channel systems. The initiative aims to enable multi-curren=
cy capabilities within the existing banking ecosystem, ensuring seamless in=
tegration across platforms such as 10x and ATLAS.</p>
<p>An initial impact analysis has been conducted based on the high-level re=
quirements documented in the below page. This assessment confirms that:</p>
<ul>
<li>Phase 1 changes will have no impact on channel systems, as the currency=
 code is already supported in both 10x and ATLAS. It's mainly display only =
change on the UI.</li>
<li>Most APIs across 10x and ATLAS platforms already support currency code,=
 minimizing the need for extensive technical uplift.</li>
</ul>
<p><a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/ARTC/ART-38922%=
3A+Detailed+Requirements+-+Foreign+currency+account+product+set+up%2C+servi=
cing+and+channels+uplifts#Channel" rel=3D"nofollow">ART-38922: Detailed Req=
uirements - Foreign currency account product set up, servicing and channels=
 uplifts - Westpac One Core - Westpac Enterprise Confluence</a></p>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
